<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="67" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/620: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-28T17:00:00-05:00">September 28, 1936—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>126. For Braden. Your 197, September 27, 2 p.m. Please cable the
                            Department the draft of any declaration or note which may be formulated
                            by the Conference as forecast in the latter portion of paragraph 3 of
                            your cable under reference before you indicate to the Conference your
                            intention to sign such declaration or note.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>